chip-desktop-configs (0.1) trixie; urgency=low

  * Initial release. Shared desktop shell configs: GTK theme (.gtkrc-2.0 + gtk-2.0
    file chooser), a compact tint2 panel (tint2rc) with a start button at the left
    that opens the openbox root menu, an openbox rc.xml binding Super+M to
    ShowMenu root-menu (what the start button fakes via xdotool), and an openbox
    autostart that launches tint2.
  * Ship the CHIP desktop wallpaper at /usr/share/chip/wallpapers/chip-desktop.png
    plus nitrogen skel configs (nitrogen.cfg, bg-saved.cfg) that point at it. The
    openbox autostart runs `nitrogen --restore` to paint it. Needs the nitrogen
    package (added to the gui flavor's package list).

 -- Ben Young <computermouth@proton.me>  Thu, 19 Jun 2026 13:00:00 -0500
